Linux:

Unzip the archive in your home directory

Copy js8msg.sh to your bin directory located in your home directory and set the executable permission.
  $ cp JS8msg/Local/js8msg.sh ~/bin
  $ chmod +x ~/bin/js8msg.sh
And rename it
  $ mv ~/bin/js8msg.sh js8msg

Copy JS8msg.desktop to your Desktop and set the executable permission.
  $ cp JS8msg/Local/JS8msg.desktop ~/Desktop
  $ chmod +x ~/Desktop/JS8msg.desktop

Lastly, set the executable permission for the main Python script.
  $ chmod +x ~/JS8msg/Bin/js8msg.py

